A well-kept garden adds beauty and calm to any Srinagar home — whether you have a small lawn in Hazratbal, flower beds in Rajbagh, or potted plants on a Nowgam balcony. Regular gardening keeps plants healthy, controls overgrowth, and prepares your outdoor space for spring blooms and summer gatherings.

## Gardening services available in Srinagar

- **Lawn mowing and edging** — neat grass, defined borders
- **Pruning and trimming** — shrubs, hedges, rose bushes, fruit trees
- **Weeding and bed clearing** — remove invasive growth, refresh soil beds
- **Planting and transplanting** — seasonal flowers, vegetables, new shrubs
- **Garden cleanup** — leaf removal, debris clearing, post-winter recovery
- **Ongoing maintenance** — weekly or monthly visits for busy households

Srinagar's seasons affect garden needs. Spring and early summer are ideal for planting and major pruning; autumn is good for cleanup before winter; regular mowing keeps lawns manageable through warmer months.

## Signs your garden needs professional help

- Grass and weeds overtaking paths and flower beds
- Overgrown hedges blocking light or views
- Dead or diseased branches on trees and shrubs
- Soil compaction or poor drainage in lawn areas
- No time to maintain after returning from travel or a busy work period

A one-time cleanup can reset the garden; scheduled visits keep it manageable year-round.

## What to tell your gardener when booking

Share the approximate garden size (lawn area in marlas or square feet), types of plants, and any specific concerns — pest damage, bare patches, or plants you want preserved. Mention access to water taps and whether green waste should be removed or composted on site.

For larger properties, a site visit or photos help the gardener estimate time and bring the right tools.

## Gardening for homes and small offices

Panun Kaergar gardening services suit residential gardens, housing society common areas, and small office courtyards. Providers are rated by customers and available across Srinagar neighbourhoods.

## Seasonal gardening tips for Srinagar

Plant cold-hardy flowers and vegetables in early spring. Water deeply but less frequently during peak summer. Mulch beds to retain moisture and reduce weeds. Trim dead growth before winter so plants stay healthy through the cold months and bounce back stronger in March.

